               <head>Works on raml divination, 2 items (a-b)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2009123573">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous collection of works on raml or divination, comprised of two heterogeneous items from separate sources. 
Volume not dated. 
Rough scribal nastaʿlīq. 
Limited annotations in margins. 
Discontinuous Persian foliation. 
Lacking original binding.
Folios detached and severely damaged at the beginning by wormholes and animal predation. 
Condition extremely fragile. 
</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_98Bx-item1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="40v">ff. 1r-40v </locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 98B* a. 
</p>
                        <p>Fragment of a treatise on raml or divination by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Defective at the beginning.
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Much of the text is missing due to severe insect and animal predation. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_98Bx-item2">
                     <locus from="41v" to="66v">ff. 41v-66v </locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 98B* b. 
</p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on raml or divination by an unnamed author who keeps withholding his identity. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
